# Through the Gates

You take the last bridge at a dead run — planks slick with spray, the river roaring white beneath you {{sfx:splash-run}} — and the thing behind you answers the river with a roar of its own. **Closer.** {{sfx:roar}}

Eekso's outer gate hangs crooked on hinges older than any kingdom you know. You shoulder through {{sfx:gate-groan}} and heave it shut, and the sound of the bar dropping into its cradle is the loudest thing in the world. {{sfx:gate-bar}}

Then — nothing. The roar does not come again.

## Inside

{{music:inside}} Silence, except the water. The river runs *under* this place — you feel it through the soles of your boots, a slow steady pulse in the stone, like standing on something's throat. {{image:art/eekso-courtyard.jpg}}

Beyond the gatehouse, a courtyard opens under broken arches — and past it, stair after stair after stair, the fortress goes **down**.

> [!dm] The gate is centuries-old Thundrak Dûrn work — but the **bar is new wood**. Someone maintains this door. (First drow breadcrumb.)

> [!dm] ⚑ If they linger at the gate: scraping, a huff of breath, then dragging footsteps that fade. It leaves. What it is stays parked ([[grill-queue]]).
